#   av "We’re not going to take them all four at once, are we?"
    av "No vamos a llevarnos a los cuatro a la vez, ¿verdad?"

# game/episode022.rpy:1599
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_a8ab0046:

#   c "No, we should try and separate them."
    c "No, deberíamos intentar separarlos."

# game/episode022.rpy:1600
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_c8a0b9f2:

#   "We continued watching the soldiers make their patrol around the compound."
    "Seguimos observando a los soldados que patrullaban por el recinto."

# game/episode022.rpy:1602
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_ad720b98:

#   "Once we’d memorized their pattern, we started to approach the compound from the side."
    "Una vez memorizado su patrón, empezamos a acercarnos al recinto desde un lateral."

# game/episode022.rpy:1603
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_e72e9abb:

#   "We were just able to hide ourselves when a patrol of two soldiers rounded the corner."
    "Apenas pudimos escondernos cuando una patrulla de dos soldados dobló la esquina."

# game/episode022.rpy:1605
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_fa046ee0:

#   "Hidden behind a pillar, I took a handful of gravel and threw it inside the pool of water nearby."
    "Escondido tras un pilar, cogí un puñado de grava y lo arrojé dentro del charco de agua cercano."

# game/episode022.rpy:1606
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_f565010d:

#   "Just like I’d hoped, one of the soldiers made their way to the pool."
    "Tal como esperaba, uno de los soldados se dirigió a la piscina."

# game/episode022.rpy:1608
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_06964aee:

#   "Céline and Aven circled back to the other soldier, while I drew my knife."
    "Céline y Aven volvieron a rodear al otro soldado, mientras yo desenvainaba mi cuchillo."

# game/episode022.rpy:1610
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_dedabe86:

#   "The soldier who’d remained behind was staring out over the landscape and didn’t notice Céline and Aven until they covered his mouth and stabbed him in the neck."
    "El soldado que se había quedado atrás contemplaba el paisaje y no se percató de la presencia de Céline y Aven hasta que le taparon la boca y le apuñalaron en el cuello."

# game/episode022.rpy:1611
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_b5d38404:

#   "He went down quietly, which was my cue to get into action."
    "Cayó en silencio, lo que fue mi señal para entrar en acción."

# game/episode022.rpy:1613
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_1b375db3:

#   "The other soldier was standing at the edge of the water and was about to turn around when I sprang up behind him."
    "El otro soldado estaba de pie en el borde del agua y estaba a punto de darse la vuelta cuando salté detrás de él."

# game/episode022.rpy:1614
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_4c284d97:

#   "I clamped my hand around his mouth and drew my knife across the soft fabric between his breastplate and helmet covering his throat."
    "Apreté la mano alrededor de su boca y deslicé el cuchillo por la suave tela entre la coraza y el casco que le cubría la garganta."

# game/episode022.rpy:1615
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_910d50e9:

#   "Blood pooled in the water as the soldier bled out."
    "La sangre se acumuló en el agua mientras el soldado se desangraba."

# game/episode022.rpy:1617
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_a0ec692a:

#   "I made my way back to Céline and Aven to take care of the remaining two soldiers."
    "Volví con Céline y Aven para ocuparme de los dos soldados restantes."

# game/episode022.rpy:1618
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_0fc1ee65:

#   c "We have to move quickly, otherwise those two remaining goons are going to find their friends."
    c "Tenemos que movernos rápido, de lo contrario esos dos matones restantes van a encontrar a sus amigos."

# game/episode022.rpy:1620
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_fb08e811:

#   "The other two soldiers were standing in front of the compound’s entrance."
    "Los otros dos soldados estaban de pie frente a la entrada del recinto."

# game/episode022.rpy:1621
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_265c328e:

#   c "I’m going to distract them, go around their position and be ready to finish them off."
    c "Voy a distraerlos, rodear su posición y estar listo para acabar con ellos."

# game/episode022.rpy:1622
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_c8dd0cbc:

#   "Céline nor Aven protested and began to sneak from our vantage point to the entrance of the compound."
    "Céline y Aven protestaron y empezaron a escabullirse desde nuestro punto de observación hasta la entrada del recinto."

# game/episode022.rpy:1624
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_eb14a2a3:

#   "I brandished my knife and made some noise to draw attention to myself."
    "Blandí mi cuchillo e hice algo de ruido para llamar la atención."

# game/episode022.rpy:1625
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_728dc737:

#   "As they turned to face my position, Aven and Céline circled round and ran up to them from behind."
    "Cuando se giraron hacia mi posición, Aven y Céline los rodearon y corrieron hacia ellos por detrás."

# game/episode022.rpy:1626
translate spanish ep022_petrarch_assault_96787061:

#   "When I saw they were in position I revealed myself just enough to get the guard’s attention."
